  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Syria Regional Refugee and Resilience Plan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Under this project, IOM aims to provide support to Syrian refugees in Turkey. In order to do so, IOM activities include: 1) the provision of comprehensive protection interventions for vulnerable refugees through emergency case management, mobile and outreach psychosocial activities, Turkish language courses and support to municipal and community centres in Gaziantep and Ankara; 2) improving access to adequate, safe, and dignified shelter conditions and contributing to community stabilization through quick impact projects; 3) increasing access to education for Syrian refugee youth through the provision of transportation; 4) facilitation of formal employment through a multi-dimensional livelihoods programme, including the provision of cash grants, job placement, and community farming; and 5) multi-sectoral social cohesion activities to reduce tensions between Syrian refugees and the Turkish host community in rural and urban settings.</narrative>
  </description>
